RACE.RACE_TEXT: LOS ALAMITOS (THOROUGHBRED) RACE 1 6F Dirt CR: 84. Maiden Special Weight Purse 45000. FOR CALIFORNIA BRED OR CALIFORNIA SIRED MAIDENS, THREE YEARS OLD AND UPWARD. Three Year Olds, 120 lbs.; Older, 124 lbs.
RACE.FOOTNOTES: STAN FROM MALIBU hit the gate but still came away fairly well, stalked up close from outside to the turn, bid three then four wide around the bend, took over in upper stretch, put away RIGHT TURN in midstretch, met the challenge from outside rivals in the final furlong and dug in late to gamely prevail. CAROL'S COMIC stalked two to three wide on the turn, tipped out in the lane, drew alongside the leader with a furlong remaining, fought between rivals late and could not get by. LORD TRIPPING broke slow and brushed with inner rival, tracked four wide into the turn, five wide into the lane, bid four deep at the eighth pole and finished gamely to the line. RIGHT TURN sped clear early, led two then three wide around the bend, lost command in upper stretch and weakened in the late stages. THE LAST ONE PERK broke a bit slow and brushed with LORD TRIPPING, chased off the rail at the back early on, went two to three wide around the bend and weakened.

ENTRY.NAME: Carol's Comic
ENTRY.OWNER: Bobby and Carol Ann Grayson Living Trust

ENTRY.NAME: Stan From Malibu
ENTRY.COMMENT: hit gate, stalked, bid 3-4wide, led, held gamely

RACE.RACE_TEXT: LOS ALAMITOS (THOROUGHBRED) RACE 2 5 1/2F Dirt CR: 78. Claiming Purse 14000. FOR FILLIES AND MARES THREE YEARS OLD AND UPWARD WHICH HAVE NEVER WON TWO RACES. Three Year Olds, 120 lbs.; Older, 126 lbs. Claiming Price $6,250 (Maiden, Claiming, And Starter Races For $5,000 Or Less Not Considered In Eligibility).
RACE.FOOTNOTES: DANCING SOUL threw her head at the start but recovered quickly, went up to vie for the lead inside a pair of rivals, cleared around the turn, opened up at the quarter pole, drifted in then back out while still well clear into the final furlong and ridden out to the wire. ROSES R BLUE was off slow to begin, chased off the rail at the back, made progress three wide around the bend and put in a belated rally to whittle the gap on the winner while gaining the place. HALF HOPING chased two wide then along the rail on the turn and was along for the show. NOISEY BURGLAR vied three deep to the turn, chased the winner three wide around the bend and weakened in the drive. NENE ROMANO took the early lead while vying between rivals up the backstretch, could not keep up with the leader around the bend, chased two wide into the lane and weakened.

ENTRY.NAME: Dancing Soul
ENTRY.OWNER: Haagsma John R and Vanderdussen Robert John
ENTRY.COMMENT: threw head start, vied inside, kicked clear, erratic str

ENTRY.NAME: Roses R Blue
ENTRY.OWNER: Knapp Steve R and Webb Steven M

RACE.RACE_TEXT: LOS ALAMITOS (THOROUGHBRED) RACE 3 6F Dirt CR: 90. Maiden Special Weight Purse 45000. FOR CALIFORNIA BRED OR CALIFORNIA SIRED MAIDENS, THREE YEARS OLD AND UPWARD. Three Year Olds, 120 lbs.; Older, 124 lbs.
RACE.FOOTNOTES: GYPSY TEARS broke inward but was quickly corrected, was closest in pursuit while racing keenly in-hand, coaxed along at the five-sixteenths pole, took over in upper stretch, cleared in the final furlong and won going away. FORDY G got bumped from outside at the start, shook it off and went up to clear the field, showed the two wide through the turn, lost command at the three-sixteenths pole and stayed on to hold the place. LUKA GRAZIE threw his head at the start to come away last, moved into range from outside, chased four wide on the turn, five wide into the stretch, kept on through the lane but could not get by FORDY G for second. GET THE GOLD broke in and bumped rival, stalked from inside, saved ground to the stretch, remained within striking distance entering the final furlong and failed to produce a bid. RIGGSALICIOUS got bumped leaving the gate, trailed on the inside to the stretch and was not a factor.

ENTRY.NAME: Riggsalicious
ENTRY.COMMENT: bumped start, saved ground, no factor

ENTRY.NAME: Get the Gold
ENTRY.COMMENT: broke in/bumped, saved ground, no bid

ENTRY.NAME: Luka Grazie
ENTRY.COMMENT: threw head start, chased 4-5wide, kept on

RACE.RACE_TEXT: LOS ALAMITOS (THOROUGHBRED) RACE 4 5 1/2F Dirt CR: 83. Maiden Claiming Purse 20000. FOR MAIDENS, THREE YEARS OLD AND UPWARD. Three Year Olds, 120 lbs.; Older, 126 lbs. Claiming Price $20,000.
RACE.FOOTNOTES: REIGN OVER ME got bumped on both sides in the beginning, chased three wide around the turn, rallied steadily under left-handed urging, drew alongside TIGER'S ARROW in deep stretch and proved best late. TIGER'S ARROW dueled for the lead from outside, inched head around the bend, cleared into the stretch, remained unchallenged into the final furlong, pressured by REIGN OVER ME with a sixteenth to go and could not fend off the winner. PAT CAN'T COUNT dueled for command inside TIGER'S ARROW, asked to keep up around the turn, lost touch in upper stretch and flattened to third. DIAMONDS PREFERRED brushed the gate and outer rival then got crowded between immediately after, chased along the inside then two wide into the stretch and lacked a bid. MOON TIME got bumped between rivals in the beginning, coaxed along chasing between rivals, got shuffled at the seven-sixteenths pole, came three wide into the lane and failed to rally. CHAIN GANG came in and bumped rival at the start, trailed early off the inside, went three wide on the turn, four wide into the drive and could not rally.

ENTRY.NAME: Diamonds Preferred
ENTRY.OWNER: Capehart Thomas R Hollendorfer Jerry Myers Jr William E Todaro George
ENTRY.COMMENT: troubled start, chased inside-2wide, no bid

ENTRY.NAME: Moon Time
ENTRY.OWNER: Osborne Candice J Saavedra Cassie Saavedra Jennifer M and Saavedra Nicholas S

ENTRY.NAME: Reign Over Me
ENTRY.COMMENT: bumped both sides start, chased 3wide, rallied

ENTRY.NAME: Chain Gang
ENTRY.OWNER: Rainmaker Racing LLC Warren Benjamin C and Warren Sally
ENTRY.COMMENT: came in/bumped start, 3-4wide, moved out, no rally

RACE.RACE_TEXT: LOS ALAMITOS (THOROUGHBRED) RACE 5 5 1/2F Dirt CR: 80. Waiver Maiden Claiming Purse 20000. FOR MAIDENS, THREE YEARS OLD AND UPWARD. Three Year Olds, 120 lbs.; Older, 126 lbs. Claiming Price $20,000.
RACE.FOOTNOTES: CORPORAL KLINGER broke a step slow then sent from outside and dueled with IRONDALE into the turn, inched ahead on the turn, maintained a short lead still fighting with IRONDALE through the drive, put that rival away late and held over EREBUS nearing the wire. EREBUS stumbled slightly but still came away quickest, raced up close two wide into the turn, spun four wide into the lane, rallied through the final furlong but was too late. IRONDALE dueled off the rail inside CORPORAL KLINGER to the turn, battled two wide around the bend, kept the pressure on through the lane and finished a clear third. WE NEED MARKETING raced up close on the inside then took hold entering the turn, moved out around the bend and came three wide into the lane, chased within striking distance then flattened in the final furlong. KING HEAT chased along the inside, lost ground around the bend and lacked a rally. BYE EVERYBODY hit the gate in the beginning and dropped back, trailed two wide around the bend, angled in at the three-sixteenths pole and weakened.

ENTRY.NAME: We Need Marketing
ENTRY.COMMENT: up close inside, took hold 7/16, inside-3wide, flattened

ENTRY.NAME: Erebus
ENTRY.COMMENT: stumbled bit, up close, chased 2-4wide, belatedly

ENTRY.NAME: Corporal Klinger
ENTRY.OWNER: California Racing Partners Ciaglia Racing LLC O'Donnell Kevin F and Savides Dome

RACE.RACE_TEXT: LOS ALAMITOS (THOROUGHBRED) RACE 6 6 1/2F Dirt CR: 81. Waiver Claiming Purse 23000. FOR THREE YEAR OLDS AND UPWARD WHICH HAVE NEVER WON TWO RACES. Three Year Olds, 120 lbs.; Older, 126 lbs. Claiming Price $12,500 (Maidens Races Not Considered In Eligibility).

CLAIM.OWNER: Tomasic Susan and Tomasic William J

RACE.FOOTNOTES: TEMBO tracked off the inside, ranged up four deep at the five-sixteenths pole, took over nearing the stretch, cleared at the three-sixteenths and was kept to task to the wire. MONGOLIAN LEGEND had to pause briefly to avoid a tight situation early then chased between foes, bumped outer rival past the seven-sixteenths pole, bid between at the five-sixteenths pole, could not keep up with the winner past the three-sixteenths pole but stayed on to hold the place. WRONG SPOT broke a step slow, trailed wide up the backstretch, came five wide into the lane, summoned a mild rally and gained the show. CAN'T RECALL forwardly placed on the inside, saved ground to the stretch, asked in the lane but flattened in the late stages. SONIC BREES chased three deep into the turn, got bumped early around the bend, bid three deep at the five-sixteenths pole, failed to keep up in upper stretch and weakened past the three-sixteenths pole. BLACK MAGICIAN showed keen early foot, led two wide then along the rail on the turn, vied inside a trio of rivals late on the bend and gave way.

ENTRY.NAME: Tembo
ENTRY.COMMENT: tracked off rail, ranged up 4deep, cleared

ENTRY.NAME: Wrong Spot
ENTRY.COMMENT: step slow, trailed, 5wide into str, mild rally

ENTRY.NAME: Mongolian Legend
ENTRY.OWNER: Gillenberg Evonne and Turner Robert V
ENTRY.COMMENT: paused early, bumped 7/16, bid between 5/16, outkicked

RACE.RACE_TEXT: LOS ALAMITOS (THOROUGHBRED) RACE 7 5 1/2F Dirt CR: 78. Claiming Purse 29000. FOR FILLIES AND MARES THREE YEARS OLD AND UPWARD WHICH HAVE NEVER WON TWO RACES. Three Year Olds, 120 lbs.; Older, 126 lbs. Claiming Price $25,000, if for $22,500, allowed 2 lbs. (Maidens Races Not Considered In Eligibility).

CLAIM.OWNER: Coast Racing Tomasic Susan and Tomasic William J

RACE.FOOTNOTES: SIGNORA MINISTER got bumped leaving the gate, stalked between foes into the turn, drifted five wide and bumped rival leaving the bend, rallied between in the lane, put a head in front at the eighth pole, dueled with TEEN DRAMA late and gamely prevailed. TEEN DRAMA got bumped on both sides at the start, stalked outside the top pair, got bumped and forced six wide leaving the turn, rallied four deep into the final furlong, fought outside SIGNORA MINISTER late and missed. SPOILED ROTTEN bumped leaving the gate, pressed the pace from outside, took over at the three-sixteenths pole, vie inside outer pair into the final furlong and yielded in the furlong grounds. SUGAR SUGAR chased three deep into the turn, three to four wide into the lane, angled out in the drive and gained the show. FRIENDLY SHUFFLE took control early from inside, maintained command two wide into the lane, lost the lead at the three-sixteenths pole and weakened. LITTLE LILIANA chased from inside and tired in the drive.

ENTRY.NAME: Spoiled Rotten
ENTRY.COMMENT: bumped start, pressed outside, led 3/16, yielded

ENTRY.NAME: Teen Drama
ENTRY.COMMENT: bumped start, stalked outside, bumped/forced 6wide, missed

ENTRY.NAME: Signora Minister
ENTRY.COMMENT: bumped start, drifted 5wide/bumped, rallied between, gamely

RACE.RACE_TEXT: LOS ALAMITOS (THOROUGHBRED) RACE 8 6F Dirt CR: 91. Allowance Optional Claiming Purse 47000. FOR CALIFORNIA BRED OR CALIFORNIA SIRED THREE YEAR OLDS AND UPWARD WHICH HAVE NEVER WON $15,000 ONCE OTHER THAN MAIDEN, CLAIMING OR STARTER OR WHICH HAVE NEVER WON TWO RACES OR CLAIMING PRICE $20,000. Three Year Olds, 120 lbs.; Older, 126 lbs. Non-winner s Of A Race Other Than Maiden, Claiming Or Starter Allowed 2 lbs. Claiming Price $20,000.
RACE.FOOTNOTES: UPWARD MOBILITY tracked two then three wide around the bend, tipped out and rallied under right-handed urging, reached the front at the eight pole and drove clear. IN VRONSKY STYLE broke well then settled in a stalking position off the inside, patiently ridden three wide through the turn, drew alongside the leader at the three-sixteenths pole, drifted in and bumped nearing the eighth pole, then got outkicked by the winner in the furlong grounds. BIG SPLASH sat off the pace early on, raced on the rail into the turn, steered out and came five wide into the drive and was along for the show. HANDSOME GARY chased four to five wide around the bend and never responded in the lane. SCARY FAST SMILE sped to the front from inside, led two wide into the stretch, collared by IN VRONSKY STYLE at the three-sixteenths pole, gave up the lead then got bumped by that rival nearing the furlong grounds and flattened in deep stretch. MY RANSOM raced outside a rival at the back into the turn, got moved out to the four path on the turn then shifted back in leaving the bend and failed to menace. MIDNIGHT LIGHTNING forwardly placed in the early going, started to weaken around the bend near the inside and tired.

ENTRY.NAME: Upward Mobility
ENTRY.OWNER: Robison J Kirk and Robison Judy

ENTRY.NAME: Big Splash
ENTRY.OWNER: Belico Racing LLC Medina Lizbeth and Pineda Milton

ENTRY.NAME: Midnight Lightning
ENTRY.OWNER: Halasz Thomas E Knapp Steve R and Lovingier Terry C

ENTRY.NAME: In Vronsky Style
ENTRY.OWNER: The Ellwood Johnston Trust and Thompson Michelle

ENTRY.NAME: Handsome Gary
ENTRY.OWNER: MJVET Stables Sides Clay and Winters Gary

RACE.RACE_TEXT: Bertrando S. LOS ALAMITOS (THOROUGHBRED) RACE 9 1M Dirt CR: 104. Stakes Purse 100000. FOR GOLDEN STATE SERIES ELIGIBLE CALIFORNIA BRED OR CALIFORNIA SIRED THREE YEARS OLD AND UPWARD. By subscription of $100 each to accompany the nomination or by supplementary nomination of $25,000 at time of entry for Non Golden State Series eligible horse s or $2,000 for Golden State Series eligible horses. $750 to enter, $750, additional to start, with $100,000 guaranteed of which $60,000 to the winner, $20,000 to second, $12,000 to third, $6,000 to fourth and $2,000 to fifth. Three year old's 120 lbs. Ol der 124 lbs. Non winners of $50,000 since March 28, 3 lbs. $50,000 since December 26, 2020, 5 lbs. Nominations closed Thusday, June 15, 2023 with 9. A trophy will be presented to the winning owner.
RACE.FOOTNOTES: KINGS RIVER KNIGHT dueled for the lead from inside into the first turn before taking control from POSITIVITY, showed the way two then three wide around the far turn, put to right-handed urging entering the furlong grounds and remained clear under steady handling. LOVESICK BLUES tracked three deep early, moved out and went four deep into the far turn, came five wide into the lane, drifted in to brush COALINGA ROAD in the lane and kept on to gain the place. COALINGA ROAD settled at the back off the rail, went four wide into the far turn, exited that bend six wide, moved into range for the final furlong but finished evenly while gaining the show honors. POSITIVITY was off alertly under coaxing from the gate, dueled from outside into the first turn then raced up close outside KINGS RIVER KNIGHT, chased that rival four wide into the lane, got brushed and floated in by LOVESICK BLUES in the stretch run and flattened out in the final furlong. DESMOND DOSS broke in to brush NONE ABOVE THE LAW at the start, stalked two wide around both turns and never responded when called upon. NONE ABOVE THE LAW brushed the gate then brushed with DESMON DOSS in the beginning, chased along the fence, cut the corner into the lane and weakened.

ENTRY.NAME: None Above the Law
ENTRY.OWNER: Robison J Kirk and Robison Judy

ENTRY.NAME: Kings River Knight
ENTRY.OWNER: Integrity Thoroughbred Racing LLC The Ellwood Johnston Trust and Tevelde Kenneth
ENTRY.COMMENT: dueled inside, cleared, led 3wide into str, responded

ENTRY.NAME: Positivity
ENTRY.OWNER: C T R Stables LLC (Calvert) and Aldabbagh Omar
ENTRY.COMMENT: up close outside, chased 4wide into str, brushed/floated in str
